{Even a passed hand can drive to slam when partner turns up with a powerhouse. Watch how Drury, splinters, and cue-bids assemble the controls one step at a time.

[BID 1S] A third-seat opening shows a real major, and after a pass the opener can be a touch light. Drury exists exactly so a passed hand can sort out how good this 1\S really is.

[BID 2C] @S @v(bid|bids) 2\C, Reverse Drury: an artificial good major raise promising about ten support points and at least three trumps. It says "I'm a passed hand, but I have a genuine raise" and asks how much extra opener holds.

[BID 3D] Opener leaps past the minimum 2\D rebid with a splinter, a singleton diamond and a sound 15-plus opening. That bid screams slam interest and pinpoints where the shortness lies.

[BID 3H] With slam now in the air, @S @v(cue-bid|cue-bids) 3\H, showing a control in hearts on the way up. Each side starts naming its top cards so they can count toward twelve tricks.

[BID 3N] Opener answers with a surplus, a slam-positive waiting move that confirms there are still extra values to spare. Nobody is backing off the slam hunt.

[BID 4D] @S @v(cue-bid|cue-bids) 4\D, a diamond control. With opener short in diamonds and this side holding a control there, the danger suit is covered.

[BID 4S] Opener settles into 4\S, marking spades as trump and inviting the final check before committing to slam.

[BID 4N] Controls all point the right way, so @S @v(bid|bids) 4\N, Roman Key Card Blackwood for spades. The keycards are the four aces plus the king of trumps.

[BID 5D] Opener's reply confirms the partnership holds the aces and the trump king it needs, with nothing crucial off the table.

[BID 6S] Everything checks out, so @S @v(bid|bids) 6\S. The combined values and located controls make this a sound small slam.

[show NS] South began as a passed hand with about ten points and three-card spade support, exactly the holding Drury was built to show. The 2\C raise, the heart and diamond cue-bids, and the keycard answer painted that hand precisely, and opposite partner's powerful opening the controls were all present. Twelve tricks roll in for 6\S making six.}
